      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The principle: if changing the value would affect model output quality, cost, or safety, it belongs in a reviewed PR \u2014 not in a flag store write or a manual console edit."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Eval Thresholds as Code"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Numeric gate thresholds belong in "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "config/eval_thresholds.yaml",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", not hardcoded in scripts. When baselines improve \u2014 after a major model upgrade, for example \u2014 the threshold change is a single PR that documents the reason and the new baseline in the commit message."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# config/eval_thresholds.yaml\n# All numeric gates live here \u2014 not hardcoded in scripts.\n\ncanary_gate:\n  neg_rate_max_by_stage: [0.10, 0.09, 0.08, null]  # null = no limit\n  quality_delta_min: -0.03     # canary minus stable; lower is worse\n  p95_latency_max_s: 4.0\n\neval_suite:\n  faithfulness_min: 0.80\n  recall_at_5_min:  0.75\n  hallucination_max: 0.10\n  answer_correctness_min: 0.65\n\nfeedback:\n  neg_rate_alert_threshold: 0.12   # Prometheus alerting rule\n  safety_feedback_spike:    5       # absolute count in 5 min"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Scripts that enforce gates read thresholds from this file rather than using magic numbers:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import yaml\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\ncfg = yaml.safe_load(Path('config/eval_thresholds.yaml').read_text())\nFAITHFULNESS_MIN = cfg['eval_suite']['faithfulness_min']   # 0.80\nNEG_RATE_MAX     = cfg['canary_gate']['neg_rate_max_by_stage'][0]  # 0.10\nLATENCY_SLO      = cfg['canary_gate']['p95_latency_max_s']  # 4.0\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Schema Validation in CI"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A malformed "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "config/models.yaml",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " that passes Git review but fails at runtime is a production outage. Add a JSON-Schema validation step that runs on every PR touching "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "config/",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " or "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "prompts/",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". The schema enforces required fields, type constraints, and value bounds before the file reaches any environment."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# scripts/validate_config.py\n\"\"\"JSON-Schema validation for config/models.yaml and config/eval_thresholds.yaml.\"\"\"\nimport yaml, sys\nimport jsonschema\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nMODELS_SCHEMA = {\n    'type': 'object',\n    'required': ['models', 'prompts', 'infrastructure'],\n    'properties': {\n        'models': {\n            'type': 'object',\n            'required': ['primary', 'judge'],\n            'properties': {\n                'primary': {\n                    'type': 'object',\n                    'required': ['provider', 'model_id', 'max_tokens'],\n                    'properties': {\n                        'provider': {'type': 'string'},\n                        'model_id': {'type': 'string', 'minLength': 1},\n                        'max_tokens': {'type': 'integer', 'minimum': 1},\n                        'temperature': {'type': 'number', 'minimum': 0.0, 'maximum': 2.0},\n                    },\n                },\n            },\n        },\n        'prompts': {'type': 'object', 'required': ['system_prompt', 'rag_template']},\n        'infrastructure': {\n            'type': 'object',\n            'required': ['vector_index_version', 'tool_registry_version'],\n        },\n    },\n    'additionalProperties': False,\n}\n\ndef validate(path: str, schema: dict) -> None:\n    data = yaml.safe_load(Path(path).read_text())\n    try:\n        jsonschema.validate(instance=data, schema=schema)\n        print(f'OK  {path}')\n    except jsonschema.ValidationError as e:\n        print(f'FAIL {path}: {e.message}')\n        sys.exit(1)\n\nvalidate('config/models.yaml', MODELS_SCHEMA)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Run "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "validate_config.py",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " as the first CI step \u2014 before any expensive prompt tests. A schema failure blocks the pipeline immediately without consuming API credits."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deployment Configuration as Code"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Kubernetes resource requests, replica counts, and environment variables belong in "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "deploy/helm-values.yaml",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", not in live cluster state. A cluster that was modified by "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "kubectl set",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " commands has configuration that is invisible to Git and will be overwritten by the next Helm deploy, causing a surprise change in production."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# deploy/helm-values.yaml\n# Kubernetes / Helm configuration for the LLM serving fleet.\n# Separate files per environment: helm-values.staging.yaml, helm-values.prod.yaml\n\nreplicaCount: 4\n\nimage:\n  repository: ghcr.io/myorg/llm-app\n  tag: \"${APP_VERSION}\"     # injected by CI from git tag\n  pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n\nresources:\n  requests:\n    cpu: '2'\n    memory: 8Gi\n  limits:\n    cpu: '4'\n    memory: 16Gi\n\nenv:\n  APP_VERSION: \"${APP_VERSION}\"\n  CONFIG_PATH: /app/config/models.yaml\n  # No secrets here \u2014 secrets come from Kubernetes Secret objects\n\nconfigMap:\n  # Mount config/models.yaml into the container at /app/config/\n  - name: models-config\n    mountPath: /app/config\n\nautoscaling:\n  enabled: true\n  minReplicas: 2\n  maxReplicas: 16\n  targetCPUUtilizationPercentage: 60"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Generating the ConfigMap from models.yaml"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "config/models.yaml",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " file needs to reach the running container. Mount it as a Kubernetes ConfigMap generated by CI from the file in Git \u2014 never copy-paste the content into the cluster directly:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# deploy/configmap.yaml  (generated by CI, not hand-edited)\n# CI creates this from config/models.yaml before the Helm deploy.\n\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: models-config\n  labels:\n    app: llm-app\n    version: \"${APP_VERSION}\"\ndata:\n  models.yaml: |\n    models:\n      primary:\n        provider: anthropic\n        model_id: claude-sonnet-4-6\n        max_tokens: 4096\n        temperature: 0.0\n    prompts:\n      system_prompt: prompts/v2.3.1/system.txt\n    infrastructure:\n      vector_index_version: 3"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Full CI Pipeline"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Wire all config-related checks into a single GitHub Actions workflow triggered by changes to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "config/",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "prompts/",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", or "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "deploy/",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". The workflow validates, tests, deploys to staging, and promotes to production with a manual approval gate."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/config-deploy.yml\nname: Config Deploy\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n    paths:\n      - 'config/**'\n      - 'prompts/**'\n      - 'deploy/**'\n\njobs:\n  validate-and-test:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n        with: { python-version: '3.12' }\n      - run: pip install pyyaml jsonschema -r requirements-test.txt\n      - run: python scripts/validate_config.py\n      - run: python scripts/check_breaking_changes.py\n      - env:\n          ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}\n        run: pytest tests/prompts/ -v --tb=short\n\n  deploy-staging:\n    needs: validate-and-test\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: staging\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - run: |\n          # Render ConfigMap from config/models.yaml\n          APP_VERSION=$(git describe --tags --abbrev=0)\n          envsubst < deploy/configmap.yaml.tmpl > deploy/configmap.yaml\n          kubectl apply -f deploy/configmap.yaml\n          helm upgrade --install llm-app ./chart \\\n            -f deploy/helm-values.staging.yaml \\\n            --set image.tag=$APP_VERSION\n\n  promote-production:\n    needs: deploy-staging\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: production   # requires manual approval\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - run: |\n          APP_VERSION=$(git describe --tags --abbrev=0)\n          envsubst < deploy/configmap.yaml.tmpl > deploy/configmap.yaml\n          kubectl apply -f deploy/configmap.yaml\n          helm upgrade --install llm-app ./chart \\\n            -f deploy/helm-values.prod.yaml \\\n            --set image.tag=$APP_VERSION\n          python scripts/tag_release.sh"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reviewing Config Changes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A config PR can be harder to review than a code PR because the impact is not visible in the diff without context. Add a diff-helper script that prints a human-readable summary of what changed between two refs:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# scripts/config_diff.py\n\"\"\"Show a human-readable diff of config changes between two git refs.\"\"\"\nimport subprocess, yaml, sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\ndef git_show(ref: str, path: str) -> dict:\n    result = subprocess.run(\n        ['git', 'show', f'{ref}:{path}'],\n        capture_output=True, text=True, check=True,\n    )\n    return yaml.safe_load(result.stdout)\n\ndef diff_configs(old_ref: str, new_ref: str) -> None:\n    old = git_show(old_ref, 'config/models.yaml')\n    new = git_show(new_ref, 'config/models.yaml')\n\n    old_model = old['models']['primary']['model_id']\n    new_model = new['models']['primary']['model_id']\n    if old_model != new_model:\n        print(f'  model:  {old_model}  ->  {new_model}')\n\n    from pathlib import PurePosixPath\n    old_pv = PurePosixPath(old['prompts']['system_prompt']).parts[1]\n    new_pv = PurePosixPath(new['prompts']['system_prompt']).parts[1]\n    if old_pv != new_pv:\n        print(f'  prompt: {old_pv}  ->  {new_pv}')\n\n    old_idx = old['infrastructure']['vector_index_version']\n    new_idx = new['infrastructure']['vector_index_version']\n    if old_idx != new_idx:\n        print(f'  index:  v{old_idx}  ->  v{new_idx}')\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    diff_configs(sys.argv[1], sys.argv[2])  # e.g. HEAD~1 HEAD"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Run "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "python scripts/config_diff.py HEAD~1 HEAD",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in the CI pipeline and post the output as a PR comment. Reviewers see "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "model: claude-sonnet-4-6 -> claude-opus-4-8",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " rather than a raw YAML diff, which makes the impact of the change clear at a glance."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Must NOT Go in Version Control"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "API keys and secrets",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 use Kubernetes Secrets or a secrets manager (AWS Secrets Manager, HashiCorp Vault). Reference them in "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "helm-values.yaml",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " as secret references, not values."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Runtime state",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 the current canary percentage or kill-switch state belongs in the flag store, not in Git. Git is for intent; the flag store is for real-time operation."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Per-user or per-request data",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 user-specific settings, conversation history, or request logs are operational data, not configuration."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Auditing Configuration Changes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Git provides a built-in audit log for every configuration change. To find when a model ID was last changed:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Find when the primary model ID last changed\ngit log -p --follow -- config/models.yaml | grep -A1 'model_id:' | head -20\n\n# Show who changed eval_thresholds and what they changed to\ngit log --oneline --follow -- config/eval_thresholds.yaml\n\n# Show the full config at a specific release tag\ngit show 'release/v4.7.2__model-claude-sonnet-4-6__prompt-v2.3.1:config/models.yaml'"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "These queries answer incident questions in seconds. Without CaC \u2014 when configuration lives in a flag store or a database \u2014 answering \"what were the model and prompt versions at 14:32 UTC on June 15?\" requires either the version registry table (if you built it) or a manual reconstruction from change logs."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Summary: ",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "bold"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Configuration-as-code for LLM systems means storing model IDs, prompt templates, eval thresholds, canary parameters, and Kubernetes deployment config in Git-reviewed files. Schema validation in CI catches malformed configs before they reach any environment. A diff-helper script posts human-readable change summaries on PRs. Mount "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "config/models.yaml",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " as a Kubernetes ConfigMap generated by CI \u2014 never edit cluster state manually. Secrets stay out of Git; runtime state (canary percentage, kill switches) stays in the flag store; everything else that controls system behaviour should be a reviewed commit."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}